fact: Dogs have an extraordinary sense of smell, with some breeds able to detect scents up to 100,000 times better than humans.
The Basenji dog breed doesn't bark like other dogs; instead, they make a unique sound often described as a yodel.
Dogs have three eyelids. The third lid, called a nictitating membrane or 'haw,' helps protect their eyes and keep them moist.
Golden Retrievers are well-known for their friendly and gentle temperament, making them great family pets.
Dalmatians are born completely white and develop their spots as they grow older.
The world's oldest known breed is the Saluki, which dates back to ancient Egypt.
The Newfoundland breed has webbed feet, which aids them in swimming, making them excellent water rescue dogs.
Pugs have a distinctive wrinkled face and a curled tail. They're known for their charming personality.
Siberian Huskies have a thick double coat that helps regulate their body temperature in extreme cold.
Chihuahuas are one of the smallest dog breeds and are named after the state of Chihuahua in Mexico.
